OL,3,CPolitician sells popular restaurant
OL,4,Csite for #1 after major fire
OL,6,FA Guernsey politician has sold the
OL,7,Fsite of a former seafront restaurant
OL,8,Ffor #1 after a major fire.
OL,10,FDeputy Yvonne Burford says she made
OL,11,Fthe decision following "the total
OL,12,Fdestruction" of St Peter Port's
OL,13,FOctopus Restaurant, which was
OL,14,Fdemolished after the blaze last year.
OL,16,FShe has passed on the land to the
OL,17,Fcurrent tenants, Delphine Pesrin-Auder
OL,18,Fand Mickael Pesrin.
